# Pegasus IA Workflow

This is secondary legacy Cursor compatibility guidance. For VS Code/Copilot sessions, prefer `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.github/instructions/`, `.github/prompts/`, and `.github/agents/pegasus-orchestrator.agent.md`.

Follow `.github/instructions/pegasus-sdd-boundaries.instructions.md`: operational instructions and internal communication use English, and generated artifacts default to English unless the user explicitly names another artifact language. Chat, persona, source language, and prior artifacts never infer an override.

Before making changes, recover context and read the local project docs in this order:

1. Recover active project/change context through `pegasus-memory-mcp` when available.
2. Search MCP memory for decisions, task progress, handoffs, observations, and learnings.
3. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/prd.md`
4. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/proposal.md`
5. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/spec.md`
6. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/design.md`
7. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/tasks.md`
8. Active-change `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/apply-progress.md` and `verify.md`

Root `docs/pegasus/*.md` files are canonical templates only. The root PRD is a natural-entry template only when no active change has been selected.

Keep work aligned with the documented scope. If requirements are missing or contradictory, update the docs or ask for clarification before implementing.

Before starting a phase or task, check MCP task progress and `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/apply-progress.md` for matching work already in progress or completed. Avoid duplicate launches.

If `pegasus-memory-mcp` is unavailable, show exactly: `El pegasus-memory-mcp no se encuentra disponible, si continuamos con eso asi, no se guardara nada de lo que hagamos en memoria persistente`. Project/change artifact work may continue, but do not claim persistent memory was saved and do not fall back to Markdown memory.

Do not write retrospective Markdown memory. `docs/pegasus/memory/` is deprecated and is not an active backend, fallback, or co-source for operational memory.

Use small slices. Each slice should have a clear goal, limited file impact, implementation status in `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/apply-progress.md`, and verification evidence in `docs/pegasus/changes/<change-id>/verify.md`.

Verify from fresh context when possible by re-reading PRD, proposal, spec, design, tasks, apply-progress, verify log, and changed files before judging completion. This is an operational rule, not a runtime guarantee.

This harness does not authorize business/domain MVP scaffolding by itself. The user/team builds the business MVP later; only create product code after the proposal, spec, design, and tasks explicitly call for it.
